  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      With this research the effectiveness of PC 6 &quot;Neiguan&quot; with conventional acupuncture in PONV
      (PostOperative Nausea and Vomiting) after laparoscopic surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
  <detailed_description>
    <textblock>
      Utilizing acustimulation, the effect of PC 6 &quot;Neiguan&quot; (acupuncture point Pericardium 6) has
      been studied in PONV . Conventional acupuncture has not been tested yet in laparoscopic
      cholecystectomy.

      The incidence of postoperative vomiting during the first 24 hours is the main outcome.
      Secondary outcomes include: complete response rate, total rescue ondansetron dose used and
      patient satisfaction with PONV management.
    </textblock>
  </detailed_description>
